</reaction>
</comment>
<comment type="cofactor">
<cofactor evidence="3">
<name>Mg(2+)</name>
<dbReference type="ChEBI" id="CHEBI:18420"/>
</cofactor>
<text evidence="3">Magnesium. Can also use other divalent metal cations, except copper and calcium.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="biophysicochemical properties">
<kinetics>
<KM evidence="3">8.7 mM for dimethylallyl diphosphate</KM>
</kinetics>
<phDependence>
<text evidence="3">Optimum pH is 8.0. Active from pH 6.5 to 9.5.</text>
</phDependence>
<temperatureDependence>
<text evidence="3">Optimum temperature is 40 degrees Celsius.</text>
</temperatureDependence>
</comment>
