<subcellularLocation>
<location evidence="3">Plastid</location>
<location evidence="3">Chloroplast</location>
</subcellularLocation>
</comment>
<comment type="tissue specificity">
<text evidence="3">Predominantly expressed in leaves.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="induction">
<text evidence="3">Up-regulated by heat stress and continuous light. Down-regulated by continuous dark and cold stress. Not induced by pathogens or treatment with methyl jasmonate or methyl salicylate.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="domain">
<text>The Asp-Asp-Xaa-Xaa-Asp/Glu (DDXXD/E) motif is important for the catalytic activity, presumably through binding to Mg(2+).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="similarity">
<text evidence="4">Belongs to the terpene synthase family. Tpsb subfamily.</text>
</comment>
